d wgini 1.1.0. Weighted Gini coefficient with Lerman-Yitzhaki source decomposition.
d
d Computes the Gini under sampling weights via the Lerman-Yitzhaki
d covariance formula, decomposes it additively by source (share x own
d Gini x Gini correlation) and by observation, reports top-share
d diagnostics (population, value, and Gini shares of the top p% and
d the Gini recomputed without them), handles negative values and
d negative-mean sources, and assigns mid-ranks at ties so results are
d exactly reproducible.
d
d Author: ChangHwan Kim, University of Kansas
d Distribution-Date: 20260717
d
F wgini.ado
F wgini.sthlp
